article.article:
This Regulation applies to feed and food within the meaning of Article 1(2) of Council Regulation (Euratom) No 3954/871 (hereinafter 'the products') originating in or consigned from Japan, with the exclusion of:
products which left Japan before 28 March 2011;
products which have been harvested and/or processed before 11 March 2011;
alcoholic beverages falling within CN codes 2203 to 2208;
personal consignments of feed and food of animal origin which are covered by Article 2 of Commission Regulation (EC) 206/2009;2
personal consignments of feed and food other than of animal origin which are non-commercial and destined to a private person for personal consumption and use only. In case of doubt, the burden of proof lies with the recipient of the consignment.

1. The competent authorities of the border inspection post or designated point of entry shall carry out:
documentary checks on all consignments of products and for which it is required to be accompanied by the declaration referred to in Article 5;
random identity checks and random physical checks, including laboratory analysis on the presence of caesium-134 and caesium-137. The analytical result has to be available within a maximum of five working days.
